You are working on TimIQ, a payroll and workforce management app.

Project root:
C:\Users\Steli\timiq

Use the existing monorepo:
- apps/api = FastAPI backend
- apps/web = Next.js frontend

Do not create a new app.
Do not move the project.
Do not delete working modules.

Backend rules:
- Use FastAPI, SQLAlchemy 2, Alembic, and Pydantic.
- Keep modules small and separated.
- Module pattern: models.py, schemas.py, repository.py, service.py, router.py, permissions.py when needed.
- Business rules go in service.py.
- Database queries go in repository.py.
- API routes stay thin in router.py.
- Add Alembic migrations for database changes.
- Never store uploaded files inside source code folders.
- Never store plaintext passwords.
- Never expose secrets or .env values.

Frontend rules:
- Use Next.js App Router and TypeScript.
- Keep pages thin.
- Put API calls in features/<domain>/api.ts.
- Follow the existing grey/white professional design.
- Keep desktop sidebar plain text.
- Keep mobile-friendly layouts.

Security rules:
- Administrator can manage all companies.
- Admin is scoped to their own company.
- Employee can only access their own data.
- Management actions must check roles on backend.

Workflow rules:
- Before editing, inspect current files.
- First produce a file/change plan.
- Wait for approval before editing.
- Make complete feature batches, not random partial patches.
- Do not mark complete until backend compile and frontend build pass.

Required backend check:
cd apps/api
python -m compileall app

Required frontend check:
cd apps/web
npm run build
